# Root environment reference (monorepo)

This file is a **catalog** of every variable used across apps and packages.
**Do not put real secrets here.** Copy the scoped templates instead:

| App / scope | Template | Notes |
|-------------|----------|-------|
| NestJS API | `apps/backend/.env.example` | Database + Supabase **service_role** (server only) |
| Expo client | `apps/mobile/.env.example` | `EXPO_PUBLIC_*` only — baked into the JS bundle |

Full semantics, validation rules, and production checklist: **`ENV_SETUP.md`**.

---

## Backend (`apps/backend`) — `process.env`

| Variable | Required | Default | Purpose |
|----------|----------|---------|---------|
| `NODE_ENV` | no | `development` | `development` \| `test` \| `production` |
| `PORT` | no | `3000` | HTTP listen port |
| `API_PREFIX` | no | *(empty)* | Global path prefix (e.g. `api` → `/api/v1/...`) |
| `DATABASE_URL` | **yes** | — | Postgres URL (`postgres://` or `postgresql://`) |
| `PG_POOL_MAX` | no | `10` | `pg` pool size (1–200) |
| `SUPABASE_URL` | **yes** | — | Supabase project URL (HTTP/HTTPS) |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | **yes** | — | **Server only** — JWT for admin auth verification |
| `CORS_ORIGINS` | **yes in production** | *(empty)* | Comma-separated allowed web origins |

---

## Mobile (`apps/mobile`) — `EXPO_PUBLIC_*` + `app.json` `extra`

| Variable | Required | Fallback | Purpose |
|----------|----------|----------|---------|
| `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` | one of API URL sources | `extra.apiBaseUrl` | Backend origin (no trailing slash) |
| `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` | *(legacy alias)* | same as above | Same as `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` |
| `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` | one of | `extra.supabaseUrl` | Supabase project URL |
| `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | one of | `extra.supabaseAnonKey` | Supabase **anon** JWT only |
| `EXPO_PUBLIC_FLAG_ANALYTICS_ENABLED` | no | `true` | Kill-switch (see `src/lib/feature-flags/flags.ts`) |
| `EXPO_PUBLIC_FLAG_REALTIME_ENABLED` | no | `true` | Kill-switch |
| `EXPO_PUBLIC_FLAG_OFFLINE_QUEUE_ENABLED` | no | `true` | Kill-switch |
| `EXPO_PUBLIC_FLAG_CIRCUIT_BREAKER_ENABLED` | no | `true` | Kill-switch |
| `EXPO_PUBLIC_FLAG_KEEP_AWAKE_DEFAULT` | no | `true` | Kill-switch |

**Forbidden on mobile:** any `EXPO_PUBLIC_*` carrying the Supabase **service_role** key. The app refuses to boot if `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` is set.

---

## Packages (`packages/*`)

No `process.env` reads — engines are pure libraries. Configuration is passed in code.

---

## Scripts / database

SQL migrations under `database/` do not read shell environment (use `psql` / Supabase SQL editor).

Python scripts under `scripts/` do not require app env vars for catalog generation.
